whereas.text:
Whereas on April 2, 2014, President Barack Obama declared Washington State in a state of major
			 disaster and approved the request made by Governor Inslee for Federal
			 disaster assistance;

Whereas in small rural towns such as Oso, Darrington, and Arlington, where this landslide occurred,
			 the impact of a disaster reaches far beyond the number of individuals who
			 lost a family member or whose property was destroyed;

Whereas this tragedy marks the third highest number of natural disaster related fatalities
			 occurring in Washington State ever, and the deadliest landslide in its
			 history;

paragraph.text:
extends thanks to the first responders, firefighters, law enforcement personnel, volunteers, and
			 medical personnel who took quick action to provide aid and comfort to the
			 victims of the landslide;
